### Network Resilience — Single-Use Token Error Handling (Meta Error 100 / 190)

Meta authorization codes are **single-use**. Re-using them returns Error 100 (`Invalid Parameter`) or Error 190 (`Access Token Invalid`). There is **no valid retry** with the same code — the only recovery is restarting the Embedded Signup flow.

**Pattern:**

```typescript
// In any service calling the Meta API
try {
  const result = await this.defLogger.request({ method: 'GET', url: '...', params: { code } });
  return result;
} catch (err) {
  if (err instanceof TokenExpiredError) {
    // Graceful failure: update Firestore status to ERROR and surface a user message
    await this.integrationDoc.set(
      { status: 'ERROR', metaData: { error: 'Token expired or already used. Please reconnect.' } },
      { merge: true },
    );
    // Do NOT retry — surface the error to the frontend via Firestore onSnapshot
    throw err;
  }
  // For non-token errors, surface generically
  throw new InternalServerErrorException('Meta API call failed.');
}
```

**State Machine for token errors:**

```
CONNECTING → (Error 100/190) → ERROR
                ↓
       User clicks "Connect" again
                ↓
          CONNECTING → ACTIVE
```

